2026-06-25 - Added quality improvement plan:
- Created docs/plan/AIPlan/07_quality_improvement.md to capture the concrete improvement path for low YOLO-seg quality.
- Focus areas: preserve more image detail, validate mask alignment, tune augmentation, compare 10/50/100 epoch runs, and evaluate recall/mAP before retraining.

2026-06-25 - Applied quality-improvement code updates:
- Updated AI/preprocess/preprocess.py to preserve original image resolution, skip defect samples with missing or empty masks, and soften offline augmentation.
- Updated AI/train/train.py to stop forcing preprocess image_size onto training, use a higher default imgsz, audit dataset quality before training, and reduce aggressive online augmentation.
- Training now writes dataset_quality_report.json under AI/train for repeatable comparison of split/class coverage and mask integrity.


2026-06-26 - Fixed preprocess filename collisions and stale outputs:
- AI/preprocess/preprocess.py:7 added `shutil` so the script can remove stale output folders before regeneration.
- AI/preprocess/preprocess.py:94 added `clear_output_dirs(config.output_root)` in `main()` so every preprocess run starts from a clean `images/`, `masks/`, `labels/`, and `meta/` tree.
- AI/preprocess/preprocess.py:127-131 added `clear_output_dirs(output_root)` to delete old generated files before recreating directories.
- AI/preprocess/preprocess.py:253 changed `write_sample()` to build names from `make_unique_sample_name(record, suffix)` instead of `Path(record.image_path).stem`.
- AI/preprocess/preprocess.py:271-274 added `make_unique_sample_name()` to include the anomaly folder name in filenames, preventing collisions between different defect types.
- AI/train/train.py:199 and AI/train/train.py:253-267 updated dataset-quality path resolution to use the same unique naming scheme when checking generated masks and labels.
- AI/train/dataset_quality_report.json was regenerated after rerunning preprocess/train smoke-test on the cleaned output.
- This fix targets false `empty_defect_masks` counts caused by overwritten or stale preprocess outputs.

